ound":true,"lemma_key":"باد","root":"بدو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1941","n2057","n3519","n3613"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perish, to die, to become extinct","examples":[{"text":"وَدَخَلَ جَنَّتَهُ وَهُوَ ظَالِمٌ لِّنَفْسِهِ قَالَ مَا أَظُنُّ أَن تَبِيدَ هَٰذِهِ أَبَدًا","english":"And he entered his garden while he was unjust to himself. He said, \"I do not think that this will perish - ever."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"apparent, evident, obvious, plain, visible"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"inhabiting the desert"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Aramaic אֲבַד (aḇad) and with Hebrew אָבַד (avad)..\n\nDerived from the active participle of بَدَا (badā, “to appear”)."},"ipa":["/baː.da/","/baː.din/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1941","headword_ar":"بَادٌّ","root":"bd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inner side of the thigh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the horseman's thigh that is next the saddle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, A, L:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part between the legs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inner sides of the two thighs are called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAd~aAni","text_ar":"بَادَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) because the saddle separates them; (IAar, M;) and if so,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAd~N","text_ar":"بَادٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or it may be a possessive epithet [meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw bad~K","text_ar":"ذُو بَدٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, L.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hasanu AlbaAd~i EalaY Als~arji","text_ar":"هُوَ حَسَنُ البَادِّ عَلَى السَّرجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a good rider upon the saddle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-  Also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse's back"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which the thigh of the rider presses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kt, T, L.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","K","T","L","S"]},{"entry_id":"n2057","headword_ar":"بَادٍ","root":"bdw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Appearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becoming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being, apparent, open, manifest, plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evident."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiYa Alr~aA^oYi","text_ar":"بَادِىَ الرَّاْىِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearance of opinion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Lh, M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to the appearance of opinion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, S, K; *) which may mean either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insincerely"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inconsiderately:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, TA:) so in the Kur xi. 29; (Zj, S;) where only AA read it with hemz: (TA:) if with hemz, it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaA^otu","text_ar":"بَدَاْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at first thought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the first opinion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S; and Lh in M, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bdA^","text_ar":"بدا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bado'N","text_ar":"بَدْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) For"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiY badK","text_ar":"بَادِى بَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiYa badK","text_ar":"بَادِىَ بَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiY badiY","text_ar":"بَادِى بَدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badowN","text_ar":"بَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiY","text_ar":"بَادِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiY","text_ar":"بَدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used as a name for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Calamity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misfortune:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it consists of two nouns made one, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEodiYo kariba","text_ar":"مَعْدِىْ كَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdK","text_ar":"بَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going forth to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiyap","text_ar":"بَادِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desert"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, * Msb, K, * TA:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiyap","text_ar":"بَادِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelling in the tents, and not remaining in his place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAduwna","text_ar":"بَادُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~FA","text_ar":"بُدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the TA erroneously said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"budFY","text_ar":"بُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudFY","text_ar":"هُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~aA='N","text_ar":"بُدَّا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badowN","text_ar":"بَدْوٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a quasi-pl. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdK","text_ar":"بَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) or is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu badowK","text_ar":"اَهْلُ بَدْوٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people who go forth to the desert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwellers in the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people of the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiyapN","text_ar":"بَادِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAduwna","text_ar":"بَادُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. people"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"migrating from the constant sources of water, and going forth to the desert, seeking the vicinity of herbage; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADirapN","text_ar":"حَاضِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAdiY","text_ar":"بَوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAdK","text_ar":"بَوَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiyapN","text_ar":"بَادِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.)"}],"source_refs":["Zj","TA","M","K","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n3519","headword_ar":"بَادَ","root":"bwd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawodN","text_ar":"بَوْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAdN","text_ar":"بَوَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byd","text_ar":"بيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3613","headword_ar":"بَادَ","root":"byd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabiydu","text_ar":"يَبِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayodN","text_ar":"بَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwdN","text_ar":"بُيُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayaAdN","text_ar":"بَيَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoduwdapN","text_ar":"بَيْدُودَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAdN","text_ar":"بَوَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawodN","text_ar":"بَوْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (CK,) the last but one disapproved by MF, (TA,) [and the last equally doubtful,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, perished;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, A, Mgh, L, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away; passed away; became cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extinct; came to an end."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdati","text_ar":"بَادَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosu","text_ar":"الشَّمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwdN","text_ar":"بُيُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun set."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","L","Msb","K","Lh","CK","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"باد","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=41206#55c644","body_html":"باد<br>عن الفارسية باد بمعنى الريح والهواء. يستخدم للذكور."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_24","lexicon_en":"Al-Tahānawī, Kashshāf Iṣṭilāḥāt al-Funūn wa-l-ʿUlūm (d. 1777 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كشّاف اصطلاحات الفنون والعلوم للتهانوي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=41206#c5bce4","body_html":"<span>باد:</span><br><span>[في الانكليزية] Wind </span><br><span>[ في الفرنسية] Vent </span><br><span>بالفارسية الريح. وعند الصوفية النصر الإلهي الضروري لكل الموجودات، ولا يوجد اسم أوفق منه للسالك.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_31","lexicon_en":"Al-Rāghib al-Isfahānī, al-Mufradāt fī Gharīb al-Qurʾān (d. c. 1109 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المفردات في غريب القرآن للراغب الأصفهاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=41206#c668c6","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">باد</span><br><span>قال عزّ وجل: ما أَظُنُّ أَنْ تَبِيدَ هذِهِ أَبَداً</span><br><span>[الكهف/ 35] ، يقال: بَادَ الشيءُ يَبِيدُ بَيَاداً: إذا تفرّق وتوزّع في البَيْدَاء، أي: المفازة، وجمع البيداء: بِيد، وأتان بَيْدَانَة: تسكن البادية البيداء.</span>"}]}}